workflow.name: AI fashion virtual try-on with image & video generation for Telegram, Discord & YouTube
workflow.description:
## üß• Virtual Try-On Image & Video Generation (VLM Run)

### üìå Overview

This n8n workflow enables a **Virtual Try-On experience** where users upload a dress image and the system:

* Combines it with a fashion model image
* Generates a **realistic try-on image**
* Generates a **fashion walking video**
* Produces **secure pre-signed download URLs**
* Automatically shares results via:

  * **Telegram**
  * **Discord**
  * **YouTube**

---

## üöÄ Use Cases

* Virtual fashion try-on
* AI fashion marketing
* Clothing e-commerce previews
* Social media fashion automation
* Influencer & brand demo pipelines


---

## ‚ú® Key Features

* üñºÔ∏è Image-based virtual try-on (model wearing the dress)
* üé• AI-generated fashion video
* üîó Multi-platform publishing (Telegram, Discord, YouTube)
* üß© Modular, extensible workflow design

---

## üß† Workflow Architecture


### üü® Input

* **Dress Image** ‚Äì Uploaded by user (Form Trigger)
* **Model Image** ‚Äì Downloaded from predefined URL
* **Prompt** ‚Äì Auto-constructed inside workflow


### üü¶ Output

* üñºÔ∏è Try-On Image (pre-signed download link)
* üé• Fashion Walk Video (pre-signed download link)
* üì§ Shared to:

  * Telegram (image/video)
  * Discord (image embed)
  * YouTube (video upload)

---

## üîê Required Credentials

You must configure the following credentials in n8n:

| Service  | Credential Type    |
| -------- | ------------------ |
| VLM Run  | `VLM Run API`      |
| Telegram | `Telegram Bot API` |
| Discord  | `Discord OAuth2`   |
| YouTube  | `YouTube OAuth2`   |

---

## ‚ö†Ô∏è Community Node Warning

> **Important:** This workflow uses a **Community Node**
> `@vlm-run/n8n-nodes-vlmrun`

### What this means:

* This node is **NOT installed by default** in n8n
* You must manually install it before using the workflow

### üì¶ Installation

Run the following command in your n8n environment:

```bash
npm install @vlm-run/n8n-nodes-vlmrun
```

Then restart n8n.

üìñ Community Nodes Documentation:
[https://docs.n8n.io/integrations/community-nodes/](https://docs.n8n.io/integrations/community-nodes/)

---

parameters.formTitle: Upload your data to test RAG

parameters.content:
# üìå Virtual Try-On ‚Äì Intro Use Case

Allow users to visualize how a dress looks on a person.
Upload model & dress images, generate a realistic try-on
image and fashion video using VLM Run with secure links.

# üü™ Merge & Aggregate

- Merge model + dress image metadata
- Aggregate items into a single payload
- Wait node ensures async safety

# üü™ Code Node & Image/ Video Download

- The **Code node** extracts the full signed URL from the webhook payload.
- It uses regex to preserve the entire Google Cloud Storage signed URL, including query parameters.
- The **Download Image** node uses this signed URL to download the processed image securely. Similarly, download generated video using **Download Video** node.

# üü© Upload to Discord, YouTube & Send via Telegram

- Send generated image/video via **Telegram**
- Post image preview to **Discord** using embed URL
- Upload generated fashion video to **YouTube**
- Uses extracted pre-signed URLs
- Enables instant sharing across platforms
